  "_notes": "Window: 2011-07-10 through 2026-06-10 (2026 World Cup, which began 2026-06-11, excluded). Sources: Wikipedia team-results pages (e.g. France/England/Spain/Belgium/Argentina/Switzerland/Norway national football team results, by decade), ESPN match pages, UEFA.com match reports, Sky Sports, Al Jazeera, and general web search cross-checks (11v11.com and worldfootball.net head-to-head pages were consulted via search snippets but blocked direct fetch/scraping, so match-by-match data came from ESPN/UEFA/news-report corroboration instead). Home/away reflects the officially listed home side for neutral-venue tournament matches (World Cup, Euros, Nations League finals) per the source reports, not true venue nationality. Pairs with zero meetings found in the window (ARG-NOR, ARG-ENG) were checked specifically for friendlies and none turned up (their only historical meetings predate 2011). Some entries carry residual uncertainty and should be spot-checked before relying on them for anything with real stakes: the exact home/away designation and venue for FRA-BEL 2015-06-07 (billed 'Belgium 4-3 France' by some outlets, played in Paris - recorded here as France home, 3-4); BEL-SUI 2016-05-28 home/away; ESP-FRA 2025-06-05 venue (Stuttgart, unconfirmed); and whether ESP-SUI, ESP-FRA, or FRA-BEL have any additional low-profile friendlies in gap years (2018-2019, 2023-2024) that didn't surface in search results. NOR-SUI's two 2012/2013 matches were initially reported by some sources as 'friendly' and others as 2014 WC qualifying Group E fixtures; treated here as WC Qualifiers per the Group E schedule."
